	"note": "Real source of SecUSo Privacy Friendly 2048, pinned at tag v1.4.0 (not the newer v1.4.2 -- the v1.4.0..v1.4.2 diff is small, real, and self-contained, so it's used as edit 01, a genuine mixed code+resources changeset; v1.4.2 alone would leave no post-pin code commit to mine). Excludes the backup/ package (BackupCreator/BackupRestorer/PFABackupService) and the custom PF2048 Application subclass -- both exist only to wire up the :backup-api submodule (org.secuso.privacyfriendlybackup.api.pfa.*), which is isolated from the game itself per corpus-app-candidates.md section 6; excluding it avoids fetching privacy-friendly-backup-api entirely. AndroidManifest.xml is scaffolding (not vendored) reflecting that exclusion: same 7 activities, no backup service, no androidx.startup provider, default android.app.Application. Needs androidx.appcompat + androidx.legacy.legacy-support-v4 + com.google.android.material + com.github.bumptech.glide:glide (plain Glide API only -- no GlideApp codegen references, so the annotationProcessor is skipped) on the compile classpath. values-night/values-v21 style overlays and the landscape (layout-land) layout variants are dropped as non-essential to compiling; every real drawable/layout/string they would have touched is still present in the default configuration.",
